## Task 1 - Domain Chosen: Retail

## Task 2: Define the Business Problem
# Problem Title

AI-Powered Customer Review Analysis for E-commerce Platforms

# Problem Description

Online shopping platforms receive thousands of customer reviews every day. These reviews contain valuable information about product quality, customer satisfaction, delivery experience, and service issues. However, manually reading and analyzing such a large number of reviews is difficult and time-consuming.

Because of this, businesses may miss important customer complaints, repeated product issues, or changing customer preferences. This can affect customer satisfaction and overall business performance.

To solve this problem, an AI-based sentiment analysis system can be developed using Natural Language Processing (NLP). The system will automatically analyze customer reviews and classify them as positive, negative, or neutral. This will help businesses understand customer opinions faster and make better decisions.

# Stakeholders / Users
E-commerce companies
Product management teams
Customer support teams
Marketing departments
Customers
Current Traditional Process

# Currently, companies mostly rely on:

Manual review reading by employees
Customer complaint tickets
Product rating summaries
Random feedback analysis

# Limitations of the Current Process
Reviewing thousands of comments manually takes a lot of time.
Human analysis may not always be consistent.
Important negative feedback may go unnoticed.
Businesses cannot monitor customer sentiment in real time.
Decision-making becomes slower due to delayed analysis.

## Task 3: Identify the AI Task Type
# AI Task Type

Sentiment Analysis (Text Classification)

# Why This AI Task is Suitable

The main goal of the system is to understand the sentiment or opinion expressed in customer reviews. Since the input data is text and the output is a category such as positive, negative, or neutral, sentiment analysis is the most suitable AI task.

This approach allows businesses to quickly identify:

Happy customers
Dissatisfied customers
Frequently reported product issues
Overall customer satisfaction trends

